result.name: Lau Sum Kee Noodle

reviews.text: Great taste. Delicious wan tan, beef brisket and tendon  together with traditional bamboo knead" noodle. Didn't have to wait too long. Recommended
Lau Sum, Mak's noodle, Mak man are the top 3 on my wanton needle soup list.

Not bad. Shrimp roe was very fragrant.

Wonton dry noodle only came with 3 wontons. The guy opposite us looked like he had more than we did :/ good wonton though.

Beef brisket dry noodle was good, tender. Very filling.

I hope we didn't get jipped with the wontons but yes, they knew we were foreigners as I had to eventually ask for the English menu (can't read Chinese).

Happy to be corrected.
I love their dumpling so much it might be one of the best dumpling u can find in sham shui po area

Excellent wonton noodle soup and dinner with steamed fish.
Unfortunately, the restaurant is closed now!
